<paragraph blockId="3.[174,1233,628,943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
D i a g n o s t i c c h a r a c t e r s. Mesonotum and pleura mostly black, scutellum yellow. Wing with wide preapical crossband (
<figureCitation box="[618,673,660,686]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[170,203,1779,1801]" captionTargetBox="[250,1160,854,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-234@1.[208,1191,839,1746]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Flies of the tribe Myopitini (1–2, 4–6): (1, 2, 4 — habitus, left; 5 — head, left, enlarged; 6 — wing): 1 — Eurasimona stigma, ♀; 2 — Inuromaesa maura, ♀, 3 — its host plant, Inula salicina, ♀; 4–6 — Myopites inulaedyssentericae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453587/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">fig 6</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis box="[685,699,661,686]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">a</emphasis>
) wider than the hyaline space between it and apical spot, broken into two spots by hyaline space on vein M; veins R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[986,1012,711,725]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">4+5</subScript>
and M convergent (
<figureCitation box="[181,236,724,750]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[170,203,1779,1801]" captionTargetBox="[250,1160,854,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-234@1.[208,1191,839,1746]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Flies of the tribe Myopitini (1–2, 4–6): (1, 2, 4 — habitus, left; 5 — head, left, enlarged; 6 — wing): 1 — Eurasimona stigma, ♀; 2 — Inuromaesa maura, ♀, 3 — its host plant, Inula salicina, ♀; 4–6 — Myopites inulaedyssentericae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453587/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">fig 6</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis box="[248,262,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">a</emphasis>
); aculeus smooth (not tuberculate).
</paragraph>
